Challenges and Opportunities: Commonsense knowledge, in particular, is genuinely open-ended, such that it depends on a number of considerations whether it makes sense to attempt to materialize relevant knowledge beforehand or rather invoke a (possibly slow) LLM on the fly.
Commonsense knowledge may also differ substantially between different cultures [Nguyen2023]. This also leads to the question of what kinds of biases are acceptable.
Finally, a long-term challenge is how to capture knowledge that is not easily expressed in language, e.g., how a robot ought to grasp different kinds of objects.